<!-- ========================================================== 
  El cool-down es un <project> 
  (distinto a las otras actividades y a los Practice Problems)
===============================================================  -->
<project xml:id="cool-cuantoMasAlta" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>¿Cuánto más alta?</title>

<statement>
  <p>La Estatua de la Libertad mide 305 pies de alto. El Puente de Brooklyn mide 133 pies de alto.</p>
  <p>¿Cuánto más alta es la Estatua de la Libertad que el Puente de Brooklyn? Explica o muestra tu razonamiento.</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>172 feet. Sample response: I drew a number line and started at 133. Then I jumped 7 to 140 and 60 more to 200. I jumped 100 to get to 300. Then, I jumped 5 more to get to 305. Finally, I added up all my jumps on the number line. <m>7 + 60 + 100 + 5</m> is 172.</p>
  </solution>


